['219.                                  \xa0                     JOHN                      GREEN                                                                                                                               was indicted for that                                                          he, at the General Quarter Session of the Peace, held by adjournment, at the New Bailey Court-house in Salford, for the County Palatine of Lancaster, on the 25th of October, 1815, was convicted of petit larceny, and was ordered to be transported beyond the seas for the space of seven years, and that he on the 25th of October, 1819                     , feloniously was at large without any lawful excuse, at \xa0St. Mary Woolnoth                                                               , before the expiration of the said term for which he was so ordered to be transported            .', 'The prisoner pleaded', '                                                                           GUILTY            . -                                                          DEATH            . Aged 27.', 'Before Mr. Recorder.']